            <p>COMBAT is a multidisciplinary and highly ambitious project on animal trypanosomosis (AT) with objectives ranging from advancing knowledge on various aspects of AT, to improvement and/or development of new control tools, up to capacity strengthening and impacting on the burden of AT in Africa. It is built upon a broad consortium having major stakeholders on board from different African AT-endemic countries and Europe. Improvements in overall veterinary health and more specifically in the control of AT at the small-holder farm level can be expected as major outcomes of this project, among others</p>
            <p> </p>
            <p> The text is well written giving a glimpse of the objectives and the broad spectrum of activities within this project.</p>
